  unique and impassioned contestants vie for the championship by spelling
  their way through vexing vocabulary, hilarious and poignant personal
  stories unfold&hellip;along with a dash of riotous audience
  participation.<br /><br />This charmingly witty and touching musical has
  entertained audiences across the world since its Tony&ndash;winning
  Broadway debut in 2005. It now returns to New York in a special 20th
  Anniversary production that celebrates the singular heart, humor, and
  verve that cemented its place in the musical theater canon. Featuring a
  Tony Award-winning book by Rachel Sheinkin (Striking 12, <em>Sleeping
  Beauty Wakes</em>) and a vibrant score by Tony Award winner William Finn
  (<em>Falsettos</em>, A New Brain), <em>The 25th Annual Putnam County
  Spelling Bee</em> is a fast-paced and funny D-E-L-I-G-H-T.</p>
END:VEVENT
